post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [war on drugs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_on_drugs) in the US was intended to be used as a tool to criminalise certain ethnic groups.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow governments to fight addictive drugs more effectively. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It would be unethical to bring in revenue from taxing drugs as it exploits those who suffer from addiction.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Economic hardship resulting from drug use would be better addressed by spending money on treatment, rather than attempting to control supply. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In India, the mental illness known in the West as [Anomie](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anomie) is cured with the drugs Soma, Amrita, and Ganja plus \\(in a more modern interpretation\\) Peyote and Ayahuasca.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Hallucinogens such as LSD and magic mushrooms have been used to create many great artworks. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'High taxes may ensure that a black market for drugs remains with all the dangers it already has. So drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A higher number of drugs users will create more work for the accident and emergency paramedic services that have to deal with people who have overdosed due to improper usage.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Recreational drugs can be used as self medication especially for those with severe mental health issues like PTSD and psychosis.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The prohibition of drugs at no time endangers the personal autonomy of the individual.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While some might overestimate the revenue, there still will be revenue. If it is 1/2 or 1/3 of those naive estimates, it is still revenue, and it still increases the government coffers.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "By legalizing and maintaining the produce of drugs for recreational use, the risk of users getting a hold of a drug falsely advertised for being something else when it's rather poisonous would never happen. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [2018 poll](https://sputniknews.com/analysis/201809141068019139-uk-drugs-policy-children-threat/) reported that children find it easier to acquire illegal substances than legal ones.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Individuals who do not seek out dangerous activities shouldn't be punished for those who do. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [war on drugs](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/War_on_drugs) in the US was intended to be used as a tool to criminalise certain ethnic groups.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The highest tax estimates of marijuana legalisation reach[$28 billion](https://taxfoundation.org/marijuana-tax-legalization-federal-revenue/) from federal revenues, business taxes and income taxes. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Private companies have a history of funding advertising supporting the use of products that are known to be dangerous to one's health, such as tobacco. I think drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If recreational drugs were legal, social events such as parties would have more variety. Drug-friendly events would also have no cause for paranoia. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This isn't possible with the most popular date rape drug alcohol, at least not in higher doses, as it's taste is quite unmistakable."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs could lead to better education on how to be safe around them. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Based on countries that have decriminalized drugs like [Portugal](https://borgenproject.org/decriminalization-of-drugs-in-portugal/), drug use has not significantly increased among the poor population, or at all.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs may be adulterated despite legalisation, like [alcoholic beverages.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20959682) I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalising all drugs may give private companies incentives to advertise/promote the use of those, potentially leading to an increase the overall drug use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a false equivalency. Providing a service or good to bolster economic growth is not the same as being forced to give your money to the government.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If you plan to drug someone with the intent of raping them, you're also able to get a hold of the something as ubiquitous as a benzodiazepine."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During prohibition, the potency of available alcoholic drinks grew significantly \\([pg. 3](https://object.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa157.pdf)\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Patients will be able to create, combine or grow their own medicines.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Some of the appeal to rebellious teens is the fact that drug use is illegal. Treating moderated drug use as a normalized behavior and treating addiction/binge use as disease takes much of the "cool" factor away. That\'s why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the long run, the standing of the U.S. government did not suffer from ending the Alcohol Prohibition in the 1930s. Any potential reputational damage from ending marijuana or other prohibitions would be fleeting.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is because the US prison system is [privately owned.](https://smartasset.com/mortgage/the-economics-of-the-american-prison-system) Incentive structures mean that running prisons can only be profitable with high rates of incarceration.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The syntheses for many illicit, addictive and recreational drugs is already known, there would be high amounts of money spent on R&D for new less addictive drugs. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The prosecution takes place after the repercussions have occurred. A ban can prevent them from ever happening.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will make it easier for researchers to study how different illicit drugs affect our brain and thereby advance our understanding of neuroscience.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Further studies on the "Rat Park" experiment discussed in the video [have found](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rat_Park#Reaction_to_the_experiment) social isolation is not necessary for addiction.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since everything is legal, users can instead choose the drugs with the most benefits and the least harms.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Through legalising drugs within a finite border, the criminal economic chain could be controlled inside that border only.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "It is hard to determine whether the drugs actually allowed these artists to make these pieces of art or whether they just happened also to be using drugs because they had troubled minds. Sober people can be great artists. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs are toxic at very low doses. These drugs can rightfully be considered weapons as well as intoxicants.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Removing some of these constraints through the legalisation of drugs could make studies more successful.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs means that they are taken, and disposed of, more safely and cautiously than in the current environment.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Medical professionals have expressed [negative attitudes](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23490450) in treating illegal substance abusers, which subsequently negatively impacts their treatment. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People who want to use drugs are largely already able to get access to them, but can have no assurance about their safety or quality. Government regulations could resolve this problem. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
